definition.value: A carbohydrate-containing antibiotic produced by the actinomyces Streptomyces lincolnensis.

The zwitterionic group formed from L-aspartic acid; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-alpha-aspartyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group and concomitant deprotonation of the gamma-carboxy group.

The zwitterionic group formed from L-glutamic acid; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-alpha-glutamyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group and concomitant deprotonation of the gamma-carboxy group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-glutaminium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-glutaminyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from glycinium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the glycyl group, formed by protonation of the amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-histidine zwitterion;  the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-histidyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-isoleucinium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-isoleucyl group, formed by protonation of the amino group.
A sulfur molecular entity containing a selenium-sulfur bond.
The organic cationic group formed from L-leucinium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-leuyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
A glutathione derivative that is glutathione in which the hydrogen attached to the sulfur is replaced by a selenol group.
A group that links two or more collagen chains to one another.
The organic cationic group formed from L-methioninium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-methionyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
A collagen cross-link having an aldimine-type structure, formed by condensation of a telopeptide lysine-aldehyde with a helical hydroxylysine residue.
The anhydrous form of the tripotassium salt of citric acid.
An organic sodium salt that is the anhydrous form of the disodium salt of ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA).

A lithium salt that is the anhydrous form of the trilithium salt of citric acid. The tetrahydrate form is used as a source of lithium for the treatment of anxiety disorders, bipolar disorder, and depression.
The inorganic nitrate salt of magnesium.
The organic cationic group formed from L-phenylalaninium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-phenylalanyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-serinium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-seryl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-threoninium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-threonyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-trytophanium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-tryptophyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-valinium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-valyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organic cationic group formed from L-asparaginium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-asparaginyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed from 2-monolysocardiolipin by deprotonation of the two phospho groups; principal species present at pH 7.3
A phytochelatin that is a pentapeptide consisting of 2 units of gamma-Glu-Cys, with a glycyl unit at the C-terminus.
A phytochelatin that is a heptapeptide consisting of 3 units of gamma-Glu-Cys, with a glycyl unit at the C-terminus.
A hydrate that is the monohydrate form of potassium citrate.
A phytochelatin that is a nonapeptide consisting of 4 units of gamma-Glu-Cys, with a glycyl unit at the C-terminus.
A collagen cross-link having an aldimine-type structure, formed by condensation of a telopeptide lysine-aldehyde with a helical lysine residue.

A collagen cross-link having an keto-imine-type structure, formed by condensation of a telopeptide hydroxylysine-aldehyde with the epsilon-amino group of a helical hydroxylysine residue and a subsequent spontaneous Amadori rearrangement of the resulting Schiff base.
A collagen cross-link having an keto-imine-type structure, formed by condensation of a telopeptide hydroxylysine-aldehyde with a helical lysine residue and a subsequent Amadori rearrangement.
A collagen cross-link formed by spontaneous reaction of a dehydro-hydroxylysino-norleucine cross-link (deH-HLNL; CHEBI:64732) with a histidine residue.
A collagen cross-link formed from two hydroxylysyl-aldehyde residues and a helical hydroxylysine residue.
A collagen cross-link formed from two hydroxylysine residues and a helical lysine residue.
A hydrate that is the tetrahydrate form of lithium citrate. It is used as a source of lithium for the treatment of anxiety disorders, bipolar disorder, and depression.
A tetracarboxylic acid anion formed by deprotonation of two of the four carboxy groups in ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA).
A collagen cross-link postulated to be formed from the reaction of a telopeptidyl lysine-aldehyde and the immature cross-link hydroxylysino-5-ketonorleucine (HLKNL, CHEBI:64749).
A 3-acyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A hydrate that is the dihydrate form of EDTA disodium salt.
A collagen cross-link postulated to be formed from the reaction of a telopeptidyl lysine-aldehyde and the immature cross-link lysino-5-ketonorleucine (LKNL, CHEBI:64750).
A 1-monoglyceride in which the glycerol moiety has (R)-configuration.
An octadecanoate ester obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of octadecanoic (stearic) acid and the hydroxy group of propanol.
A phytosterol consiting of ergostane having double bonds at the 5,6-, 7,8- 9,11- and 22,23-positions as well as a 3beta-hydroxy group.
An  EC 3.1.4.* (phosphoric diester hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of phosphatidylinositol-specific phospholipase C (EC 3.1.4.11).
A glycerol 1-phosphoserine(1-) in which the glycero portion has R-configuration and the serine moiety has L-configuration.
A group that carries an overall positive charge.
A group that carries an overall negative charge.
